# Event-Driven Architecture & CQRS Patterns

## CQRS Command-Query Separation

**Commands** (writes) and **Queries** (reads) are strictly separated.

### Command Pattern

Commands **mutate** state and return the created/updated entity or ID. Place in `<module>/commands/`.

```typescript
// create-deal.command.ts
export class CreateDealCommand {
  constructor(public readonly dto: CreateDealDto) {}
}

// create-deal.handler.ts
import { CommandHandler, EventBus, ICommandHandler } from '@nestjs/cqrs';

@CommandHandler(CreateDealCommand)
export class CreateDealHandler implements ICommandHandler<CreateDealCommand> {
  constructor(
    private readonly dealRepo: DealRepository,
    private readonly eventBus: EventBus,
  ) {}

  async execute(command: CreateDealCommand): Promise<Deal> {
    const deal = await this.dealRepo.create(command.dto);
    
    // ✅ Publish event after mutation
    this.eventBus.publish(new DealCreatedEvent(deal.id, deal.pospId, deal.status));
    
    return deal;
  }
}
```

### Query Pattern

Queries **read** state and return DTOs. Place in `<module>/queries/`.

```typescript
// get-all-deals.query.ts
export class GetAllDealsQuery {
  constructor(
    public readonly pospId?: string,
    public readonly status?: DealStatus,
  ) {}
}

// get-all-deals.handler.ts
import { QueryHandler, IQueryHandler } from '@nestjs/cqrs';

@QueryHandler(GetAllDealsQuery)
export class GetAllDealsHandler implements IQueryHandler<GetAllDealsQuery> {
  constructor(private readonly dealRepo: DealRepository) {}

  async execute(query: GetAllDealsQuery): Promise<Deal[]> {
    return this.dealRepo.findAll({
      pospId: query.pospId,
      status: query.status,
    });
  }
}
```

### Service Layer Integration

Services orchestrate commands/queries via `CommandBus` and `QueryBus`.

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class DealService {
  constructor(
    private readonly commandBus: CommandBus,
    private readonly queryBus: QueryBus,
  ) {}

  async createDeal(dto: CreateDealDto): Promise<Deal> {
    return this.commandBus.execute(new CreateDealCommand(dto));
  }

  async findAll(filters: DealFilters): Promise<Deal[]> {
    return this.queryBus.execute(new GetAllDealsQuery(filters.pospId, filters.status));
  }
}
```

## Event-Driven Architecture

### Event Structure

Events are **immutable** facts that occurred. Place in `<module>/events/`.

```typescript
// deal-created.event.ts
export class DealCreatedEvent {
  constructor(
    public readonly dealId: string,
    public readonly pospId: string,
    public readonly status: DealStatus,
    public readonly occurredAt: Date = new Date(),
  ) {}
}
```

**Rules**:
- Use past tense: `DealCreatedEvent`, `UserRegisteredEvent`
- Include all data needed by listeners (avoid requiring DB lookups)
- Include `occurredAt` timestamp
- Make all properties `readonly`

### Event Publishing

Publish events **after** successful mutation, **before** returning.

```typescript
@CommandHandler(UpdateDealCommand)
export class UpdateDealHandler implements ICommandHandler<UpdateDealCommand> {
  constructor(
    private readonly dealRepo: DealRepository,
    private readonly eventBus: EventBus,
  ) {}

  async execute(command: UpdateDealCommand): Promise<Deal> {
    const existing = await this.dealRepo.findById(command.id);
    const updated = await this.dealRepo.update(command.id, command.dto);

    // ✅ Publish event if status changed
    if (existing.status !== updated.status) {
      this.eventBus.publish(
        new DealStatusChangedEvent(
          updated.id,
          existing.status,
          updated.status,
        ),
      );
    }

    return updated;
  }
}
```

### Event Listeners

Listeners react to events. Place in `<module>/listeners/`.

```typescript
// deal-events.listener.ts
import { EventsHandler, IEventHandler } from '@nestjs/cqrs';

@EventsHandler(DealCreatedEvent)
export class DealCreatedListener implements IEventHandler<DealCreatedEvent> {
  private readonly logger = new Logger(DealCreatedListener.name);

  constructor(
    private readonly notificationService: NotificationService,
  ) {}

  async handle(event: DealCreatedEvent): Promise<void> {
    this.logger.log(`Deal created: ${event.dealId}`);
    
    // Side effects: notifications, analytics, etc.
    await this.notificationService.notifyPospOfNewDeal(event.pospId, event.dealId);
  }
}
```

**Rules**:
- Listeners are **side effects** — logging, notifications, analytics, cache invalidation
- Listeners **must not** throw errors that break the main flow
- Wrap listener logic in try-catch and log errors
- Keep listeners **idempotent** (safe to replay)

### Multiple Listeners

Multiple listeners can subscribe to the same event:

```typescript
@EventsHandler(DealCreatedEvent)
export class DealAnalyticsListener implements IEventHandler<DealCreatedEvent> {
  async handle(event: DealCreatedEvent): Promise<void> {
    // Track deal creation in analytics
  }
}

@EventsHandler(DealCreatedEvent)
export class DealNotificationListener implements IEventHandler<DealCreatedEvent> {
  async handle(event: DealCreatedEvent): Promise<void> {
    // Send notification
  }
}
```

## Module Registration

Register all commands, queries, and listeners in the module:

```typescript
@Module({
  imports: [CqrsModule],
  controllers: [DealController],
  providers: [
    DealService,
    DealRepository,
    // Commands
    CreateDealHandler,
    UpdateDealHandler,
    DeleteDealHandler,
    // Queries
    GetAllDealsHandler,
    GetDealByIdHandler,
    // Listeners
    DealCreatedListener,
    DealStatusChangedListener,
    DealAnalyticsListener,
  ],
})
export class DealModule {}
```

## Controller Pattern

Controllers delegate to service, which uses CommandBus/QueryBus:

```typescript
@Controller('api/deals')
export class DealController {
  constructor(private readonly dealService: DealService) {}

  @Post()
  async create(@Body() dto: CreateDealDto): Promise<Deal> {
    return this.dealService.createDeal(dto);
  }

  @Get()
  async findAll(@Query() filters: DealFiltersDto): Promise<Deal[]> {
    return this.dealService.findAll(filters);
  }
}
```

## Anti-Patterns

### ❌ BAD: Direct repository calls in service
```typescript
@Injectable()
export class DealService {
  constructor(private readonly dealRepo: DealRepository) {}

  async createDeal(dto: CreateDealDto) {
    return this.dealRepo.create(dto); // ❌ No CQRS, no events
  }
}
```

### ✅ GOOD: Use CommandBus
```typescript
@Injectable()
export class DealService {
  constructor(private readonly commandBus: CommandBus) {}

  async createDeal(dto: CreateDealDto) {
    return this.commandBus.execute(new CreateDealCommand(dto));
  }
}
```

### ❌ BAD: Mixing queries and commands
```typescript
// ❌ Don't put queries in command handlers
@CommandHandler(CreateDealCommand)
export class CreateDealHandler {
  async execute(command: CreateDealCommand) {
    const deals = await this.dealRepo.findAll(); // ❌ Query in command
    // ...
  }
}
```

### ❌ BAD: Event listeners mutating primary state
```typescript
// ❌ Don't use listeners for critical state mutations
@EventsHandler(DealCreatedEvent)
export class DealCreatedListener {
  async handle(event: DealCreatedEvent) {
    await this.dealRepo.update(event.dealId, { processed: true }); // ❌
  }
}
```

### ✅ GOOD: Use commands for mutations
```typescript
// ✅ Create a separate command for critical mutations
@CommandHandler(CreateDealCommand)
export class CreateDealHandler {
  async execute(command: CreateDealCommand) {
    const deal = await this.dealRepo.create(command.dto);
    
    // If processing is critical, do it in the command
    await this.dealRepo.update(deal.id, { processed: true });
    
    this.eventBus.publish(new DealCreatedEvent(deal.id));
    return deal;
  }
}
```

## Benefits

- **Separation of Concerns**: Clear boundaries between reads and writes
- **Scalability**: Queries can be optimized independently (caching, read replicas)
- **Auditability**: Events provide audit trail of all changes
- **Extensibility**: Add new listeners without modifying existing code
- **Testability**: Commands, queries, and listeners are isolated and easy to test
